It's his stupid brother's fault!

1398
01:28:36,087 --> 01:28:37,756
I understand. I can help you.

1399
01:28:37,964 --> 01:28:40,508
But you're gonna have to let
me know who it is we're talking about

1400
01:28:40,717 --> 01:28:43,261
- and what's about to happen.
- My boyfriend.

1401
01:28:44,095 --> 01:28:47,474
He was talking about killing a cop.

1402
01:29:20,382 --> 01:29:22,884
You hear that?
You know what that is?

1403
01:29:23,093 --> 01:29:25,637
That's a damn beautiful sound.

1404
01:29:25,845 --> 01:29:27,847
Those are my boys coming.

1405
01:29:56,793 --> 01:29:59,045
So, what do we do now?

1406
01:29:59,921 --> 01:30:01,756
We get out.

1407
01:30:07,137 --> 01:30:10,015
Jesus Christ! What is that?
Wha...? What's that?

1408
01:30:10,223 --> 01:30:14,227
It's ice fishing.
Tommy there is part Eskimo.

1409
01:30:27,741 --> 01:30:29,367
No.

1410
01:30:32,579 --> 01:30:34,164
It's not looking good
for you, homeboy.

1411
01:30:34,581 --> 01:30:36,624
We'll see if they're still your boys
after they find out

1412
01:30:36,833 --> 01:30:39,919
you killed your partner Green,
homeboy.

1413
01:30:40,420 --> 01:30:41,921
That's your angle, huh?

1414
01:30:42,130 --> 01:30:45,425
You gonna walk out there
and tell them I killed Green.

1415
01:30:47,010 --> 01:30:48,595
That's your story?

1416
01:30:48,803 --> 01:30:51,264
- It has the advantage of being true.
- So what?

1417
01:30:52,265 --> 01:30:54,476
I killed my partner.

1418
01:30:55,685 --> 01:30:57,937
I could kill the whole
damn police department

1419
01:30:58,146 --> 01:30:59,606
if you were the only witness.

1420
01:31:00,231 --> 01:31:02,233
